Both average and count are an integer. So their division is also an integer.
Use cast operator

    average=(float)total/count
or

    average=total/(float)

`total / count` is an integer division.  The remainder  of the quotient is lost before the assignment to the `float` object  `average`.

Instead, perform floating point division.

----

In general, code should avoid casts.  Use them sparingly.  Casting can readily hide issues too.

Consider gentler means  like introducing a floating point constant in the computation.

    1.0 * total / count

Here the is also little need to the smallish `float` versus C&#39;s more work-horse floating point type `double`.  Various large `int` values will not save exactly in a `float`.

Note that `printf(&quot;%.2f\n&quot;, average);` converts `average` to a double before passing it to `printf()`.

Watch out for `/ 0`

